<Review>Fun place to stop and check out the sculptures peppered throughout the grounds around Christmas Circle Drive.

Though the attractions were closed to the public we pulled over and watched them from a distance. The pictures below were taken last fall when we were there pre COVID.

If you are headed to Palm Springs from the south end, stop and check it out. Neat little desert town with a few dining options.<//Review>< Pics>

<text>We loved stopping here after hiking to have an amazing picnic and a beautiful 360 view of mountains and beauty all around us.  We even enjoyed free WiFi: password on bathroom mirrors. I have two questions though:

1. Why is it called Christmas Circle Park?

2. Why doesn't more towns have a cool park like this in the center of them?

< Review>
Christmas circle in Borrego always reminds me of that scene in the Griswold's European vacation.  Stuck in the endless circle & can't get out. Haha!
With that being said, it is a cool spot to have a packed lunch or enjoy a snack you picked up in town, while taking in the scenery.   We normally stop in that area during the winter months. We like to check out the artworks that are around the area. Most can be seen from the roadway but, there are well traveled trails to get up close. Fun way to engage with nature & explore new parts of the desert. Most standard car's can make it. Just go slow & take ur time.  Borrego springs is a beautiful area, help keep it that way. Take out what u bring in.  It takes a tribe.  We always enjoy our visits down there. I'm sure you will too!</Review>

Erica Peterson< /name>

< time>
1572689038132<//time>
<pictures>None<//pictures>< rating>
5<//rating>
< Review>
Every year at the end of October, "Borrego Days" begins. This event has been reoccurring for over 50 yrs. The 3 day event begins on a Friday and lasts through Sunday evening. There is an annual "Miss Borrego Springs" Pageant prior to Fridays kickoff and then on Saturday there is a 9 am Parade. Thru the weekend, there are vendors selling various items such as handmade jewelry, drinks, food, speciality items, toys, a jumper for kids ALL & more at Christmas Circle! I went on Sunday this year and there was a very popular & famous live band from Sinaloa, Mexico. Great Music! Lots of people dancing! Enjoying themselves and sharing with one another! After all, we are a small town of approx. 3500 people. There are many restaurants you can eat at when you come to Borrego. Like Carlees, which has a bar, pool tables, Dinning area, Music & Karioke. There's Pablitos Mexican, Jilbertos Taco Shop, Kendall's Cafe (Which is my favorite place in Borrego, eat in or order by phone for pick up, carry out) El Borrego Mex, Red Ocotillo ( the Hamburgers are SUPERB), Palm Canyon Resort, which just recently changed there menu (and I think it was great and easier to order) and prices very reasonable. They have a Saloon where you can order n eat there as well.. (employees seem intuitive and always smiling) So, put it in your calendar for next year and come on down and enjoy, relax, unwind and share a memorable weekend as a family!!!</Review>

< text>
have been avoiding going to a dentist for a number of years and when I finally had a dental emergency that needed immediate attention I chose the most convenient option. I work in the same building as Dr. McElroy and the office accepts my insurance. The reviews on the office were excellent and while I have a great deal of anxiety about going to the dentist I was already put somewhat at ease by the reports that this practice catered to my specific needs. I was wholly unprepared for the ease and level of service that I received on my first visit. Everyone from the front desk staff, to the assistant, to the doctor himself were so professional and understanding of my personal needs. The office is beautiful, clean, and inviting and has some of the nicest folks working there that I could ever have hoped for. They have features in place that help even an anxious person like myself find a level of comfort that I have never experienced at another practice in my entire life. The technology and equipment used was top of the line and made the entire experience so much easier and pain free. They quickly diagnosed my issue and set up a convenient appoint to correct the problem. Susan was an absolute gem and talked me through the billing process, offering me payment options that were realistic and tailored to my needs. When I returned for the procedure Dr. Haught took over and treated me with so much kindness and respect, and really made the entire procedure so painless and easy. Susan then walked me through my follow up plan for getting back to a positive place with my dental health without ever trying to upsell or push me to do any procedure that I was uncomfortable with. I love this office and I can't possibly give a higher recommendation. Thank you Smiles by Design, you made a really scary event for me turn into an incredibly positive experience. My friends and family will be coming to see you soon!<//text>

<username>Brandon Mcelroy</username>< Review>
Recently I visited Smiles By Design in order to fix my two front teeth that had been greatly damaged from childhood events. Both of my front teeth were split in half due to several accidents and I have always dreaded getting them redone. When they were originally repaired numerous years ago, the doctor restored them with composite bonding material but over the years they discolored. Therefore, I was in search of a doctor who could restore my two front teeth to the ideal pearly white color and tooth shape. I determined that Dr. McElroy fit my criteria and allowed him to proceed to restore my two front teeth. After over 5 years of hiding my smile because of my teeth discolored, I am more than happy to smile for anyone now. Dr. McElroy provided me with two luminous white porcelain veneers and a whitening session that has improved my smile greatly, while granting me back the confidence to smile at all times again. To say I am grateful for this procedure is an understatement and I am excited for my next appointment with Smiles by Design.< /Review>

<Response>{'time': 1504725821769, 'text': 'Thank you very much David. It was an honor to serve you.'}</Response>< Text>
From the moment you enter the handsome office, take a tour of the facilities, view the awards and philanthropic outreach photos, you feel as though you're a part of a family. Family Dentistry, that is. I'm sure Dr. McElroy, or Dr. Mac to his friends & staff, didn't get to where he is today without knowing a thing or two about having a charming chair-side manner. He's as comfortable as a pair of your favorite shoes. I found this office by looking specifically for a "Cerec-Certified Dentist." Mission accomplished. While I'm not an employee, I am an online host for Dentsply Sirona, the American dental equipment maker and leading dental consumables producer that markets its products in over 120 countries. Knowing a company with a background as solid and reputable as they are, I was certain a dentist who believed in their products would be a dentist I could believe in. Here's my bottom line: Being new members of the Encinitas community, my wife and I are big supporters of "local" and do what we can to improve the business of "the little guy." While I'm not calling Dr. Mac a little guy, he is a local guy with a big heart. Check him out today!</Text>

< Review>
Just left MJ's, first time there, and I am very pleased with how they take care of pets. Dropped our dogs off and had them back in a couple hours. They didn't have to wait in kennels for several hours. The haircut for my doodle was spot on. Doodles aren't the easiest to cut and the groomer did a terrific job. We will definitely be returning to MJ's. I highly recommend them.</Review>

Today, I had my behind the wheel test at the San Clemente DMV. I had signed up for the varsity DMV package. I got a call from the varsity instructor Ed yesterday confirming the pickup  time and what to expect. Ed showed up a few minutes early this morning and he was very courteous and professional. He let me drive the car to get warmed up and also gave me last minute very helpful tips. The DMV test went fine and I passed easily. I would like to thank varsity driving school and specially Ed for helping me through the process of learning driving. Coming from outside the US I had to learn the driving and get to understand the rules. Ed is awesome and makes things very easy and simple for me. I also want to thank the varsity office staff. They were very pleasant and getting driving lesson appointments was an easy process. I would rate my overall experience 10/10 üëç

<Name>Vera B.< /Name><userid>111142273353926682005< /userid>< review>
I would highly recommend Varsity. I moved to CA from Manhattan (NYC) and had to learn how to drive at a ripe age!  I did a careful research on line before I picked Varsity (Irvine) based on reviews, instructor profiles and the smooth communication with the scheduling office. I took about 30 lessons with Varsity over the course of 2.5 months and received my driver‚Äôs license at first try.  I followed up with a few lessons to improve on freeway driving.
The administration/scheduling office is very competent and incredibly efficient and responsive. They explained the process of getting the license, helped me set up a packed schedule, and were great in accommodating changes.  They are excellent and very organized in communicating schedule and sending lesson reminders.
I had the pleasure of meeting many of the Varsity instructors - all incredibly knowledgeable and professional, each with their style, insights and advice that were remarkably helpful. Each instructor explained things very well and in ways that clicked, and I will remember. A big shout-out and huge thank you to Isaac and Jose with whom I had the most lessons! A big thank you to Michelle, Arturo, Daisy, Kam George, and everyone else. George was a wonderful positive calm presence for the test. I very rarely (almost never) write reviews, but realized how helpful other people‚Äôs reviews of driving schools were for me, so here you go.</review>

I will just copy my review on Yelp.

That coach just kept telling me that I am not good enough and asked me to practice a lot of meaningless task, like driving the previous student home, and go to pick up his next student.....(Can you believe that? it would take almost 1 hour from my 2 hours session). He made me nervous about my skill, and I was such a fool that I took 5 classes with him. He just would not stop and made me spend more money...

After finding my confidence in driving was nearly lost, I decided to find Tony again. He encouraged me a lot and helped me pick up my confidence again. I am going to take the test next week. I signed up for 6 hour refresher lessons after reading reviews on Yelp, with a constraint of all 6 hours within less than a week of time. The booking process was simple, efficient and fast and Katie, my instructor, was on time, everyday in front of my door.

He guided me throughout the training on how to drive as a ‚Äúdefensive, safe driver.‚Äù I learned to put into practice everything I learned from the dmv handbook. I even learned how to properly handle and turn the steering wheel, how to properly use the brakes, and how to properly accelerate and decelerate.

Thanks!

<Rating>5<//Rating><Text>I work a lot of hours and had to find a school that could teach my daughter how to drive and take her out enough to really learn how to negotiate Orange County roads.  So I signed her up for the Varsity Driving Academy their 20+ hour behind-the-wheel package.  They took her driving booth in the daytime and at night, which gave her the confidence and experience to pass the DMV driving test the first time.

Additionally, the office staff is very helpful.  We especially liked Ms. Katie Korona, who helped us pick the right package to meet our needs.  She also coordinated a driving schedule that worked extremely well with my daughters‚Äô availability.  Her customer services skills are exceptional.

Our favorite instructor ‚ÄúGeorge‚Äù has nerves of steel, and nothing fazes him.  I personally could not handle the experience of having my daughter behind the wheel.  She was not very good at first.  After a few classes with him, she improved immensely.  George is very good at pointing out why one needs to follow certain driving rules on the freeway versus streets.  This is really important because explaining the reasoning behind certain rules of the road (DMV) helps a student remember it when it comes time to drive and to take the DMV driving test.  His straightforward manner really helped my daughter improve her driving skills.   With all the accidents I witness every day driving home in traffic, I am so grateful to George and the other instructors for giving my daughter the driving skills to hopefully avoid being in an accident.  They took her onto the 22 freeway, the 55 freeway (which is known for its daily quota of accidents) and the 405 freeway several times so she would have the skills necessary to drive on them.  My daughter got her license but wanted a few extra lessons on dealing with nighttime traffic on the freeway, so I signed her up for 6 more hours.  This has been an excellent investment.  The night time driving teachers are also great and since most of them are at the high traffic hours, my daughter got the skills and confidence to help her feel better about driving in traffic.

As for the cars, they are each a  bit different in size, which is great.  My daughter learned about the differences between the vehicles and how they can affect how she changes lanes (in heavy traffic) and the different blind spots.  Varsity Driving Academy really took the time out to plan an excellent driving sessions for my daughter to help her learn the skills she needed to drive in Orange County.  I would recommend this program to any parent who is nervous about their child driving in Orange County or who want the best possible instructors for their child.<//Text><pictures>None< /pictures><Resp>None< /Resp><Gmap_id>0x80dcddb056dafeab:0x86dae8fdfafcc2f2< /Gmap_id></record>

<review>If you're looking for a driver's ed class, then look no further. VDA excels in helping you master the basics of operating a motor vehicle, and they do this by the sample assessments that you take in abundance, the videos they show you in class, and the very informative teacher that helps you throughout.

The first taste I got of VDA was when I called to set myself up to join the in-class program. I spoke on the phone with Caitlin, who made my sign-up was really easy. She was very friendly on the phone, and I was surprised by how smooth the sign-up process went.

Katie was my teacher and will be my driving instructor when I pass the written test. Katie answered all the questions I had, at the highest degree of knowledge. As a whole, VDA's environment was very friendly. Oftentimes, the driving instructors would pass through and they all added to the friendly environment.
